Being one of the earliest Drupal adopters http://drupal.org/user/11, I started using Drupal from version 2.0. Along the way I created several Drupal core themes, was close to the birth of Druplicon and helped to improve Drupal user experience. Nowadays I consult the new generation of Drupal users and collect the digital memorabilia from Drupal past.

I blog at http://kristjanjansen.ee, piping it's Drupal-related content to Drupal Planet.

• Founder and Project Lead of Drupal
  • Product Lead of Drupal Starshot / Drupal CMS
  • Co-founder and Board Member of the Drupal Association
  • Co-founder, CTO and CSO of Acquia

Drupal developer (PHP, MySQL/PostgreSQL) and implementer since 2000.

field_drupal_contributions.value:
Being one of the earliest Drupal adopters http://drupal.org/user/11, I started using Drupal from version 2.0. Along the way I created several Drupal core themes, was close to the birth of Druplicon and helped to improve Drupal user experience. Nowadays I consult the new generation of Drupal users and collect the digital memorabilia from Drupal past.

I blog at http://kristjanjansen.ee, piping it's Drupal-related content to Drupal Planet.

Moshe has been a consistent contributor to Drupal core and Contrib since November 2001. As such, he has pretty much touched the whole core code. He maintains the user.module, the bootstrap code, and the groups.drupal.org web site. See Moshe's CV page here on drupal.org
